During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer announced that President Trump will be embarking on his first foreign trip in one week. The trip will include visits to Saudi Arabia, Israel, Rome, Brussels, and Sicily. The President's goals for the trip include reaffirming America's global leadership, building key relationships with world leaders, and promoting a message of unity among different faiths. The President will also address issues such as terrorism, trade, and security during the trip. Spicer also discussed other topics such as the FBI director selection process and recent developments in trade with China.